title: Finland Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Finland Three Month Interbank Rate increased to 1.74 percent on Monday November 7 from 1.73 percent in the previous day. Interbank Rate in Finland averaged 0.45 percent from 1987 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 16.14 percent in December of 1989 and a record low of -0.61 percent in December of 2021. In Finland, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Finland Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: European Banking Federation
